@B Funny, that “recent chewy Tuesday” took me about a minute longer than my Tuesday average, and didn’t even stand out to me as especially difficult until I came to the comments section.

It’s wild how much subjective difficulty varies across the solving population…and yet, how quick people are to make inductive leaps based upon their personal experiences.

Incidentally, it would be so fun if the NYT would publish solving stats for puzzles (average times, variance relative to individual daily averages, etc).

@Steve L 

Thanks! I created an xwstats account like a year ago, had an issue linking my NYT account, and forgot all about it. This is great!

At least on paper, today’s puzzle came out right around average, with 52% of solvers faster than their Friday averages.

